most conversant and active research in the field of Jeffers studies. The critiques speak to the nature of Jeffer's poetry- how it challenged both the minds and hearts of its readers and prompted them to carefully define their own values and authentically find their own center.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aBeers, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrophy, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEverson, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlaser, Kirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothman, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoldofsky, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVardamis, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZaller, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329657640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823296576423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823296576/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK